answers.body_markdown:
The basic issue is that without proper synchronization, how writes to memory may manifest in different threads.  The classic example:

    a = 1;
    b = 2;

If you do that on one thread, a second thread may see b set to 2 before a is set to 1.  Furthermore, it&#39;s possible for there to be an unbounded amount of time between a second thread seeing one of those variables get updated and the other variable being updated.

